                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/91: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-23T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. Your 159, February 19, 6 p.m. Department approves method of procedure
                    outlined in paragraph 2 of your telegram and you are authorized to instruct
                    consuls accordingly requesting them to inform local Chinese authorities. You are
                    also authorized to inform your colleagues of this Government’s decision in this
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
